msgid "Since Python 3.0, all strings are stored as Unicode in an instance of the :class:`str` type. *Encoded* strings on the other hand are represented as binary data in the form of instances of the :class:`bytes` type. Conceptional, :class:`str` refers to *text*, whereas :class:`bytes` refers to *data*. Use :meth:`str.encode` to go from :class:`str` to :class:`bytes`, and :meth:`bytes.decode` to go from :class:`bytes` to :class:`str`."
